[G7]By her a cradle stands [C]empty
And [D7]o'er it she sobs and she [G]moans
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
My husband he no longer loves me
His love and our dear baby died
I'll [G7]leave him at home [C]forever
And [D7]out in this old world [G]abide
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
She packed baby's things in the bundle
While the tears rolled down her cheeks
[G7]I never no never would [C]leave him
If [D7]ever a kind word he'd [G]speak
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
Just then the door softly was opened
A man took the bundle away
He [G7]laid the things out on the [C]table
And [D7]softly to her he did [G]say
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
One little stocking [D7]for you dear
One little blue shoe is [G]for me
The baby's wrap and its [C]smallest cap
[A7]We'll keep in memo[D7]ry
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
[G]One lock of hair is [D7]for you dear
See how the golden curls [G]shines
We'll keep a smile while [C]she sleeps for
[D7]She is the tie that [G]binds
{end_of_verse}





